# Optional runtime + build env for the self-hosted GTNH Factory Flow service.
#
# Install to /etc/gtnh-factory-flow.env. Nothing here is secret unless you add
# analytics keys (then chmod 600). Loaded by deploy.sh at BUILD time and by
# systemd (EnvironmentFile=) at RUNTIME. You can omit this file entirely when you
# self-host the dataset and don't use analytics.

# ── Dataset source ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Proxy mode (easiest): forward dataset files AND /api/datasets/* to an upstream
# deployment, so this box needs no local dataset volume. See next.config.ts.
#GTNH_DATASET_BACKEND_URL=https://gtnh.samiracle.fr
#
# Self-host mode: leave the above commented, populate
#   /srv/data/gtnh-factory-flow/datasets/gtnh
# and deploy.sh links it into the build. The default manifest URL already points
# there, so no var is needed:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_GTNH_DATASET_MANIFEST_URL=/datasets/gtnh/datasets.manifest.json

# ── Analytics (optional, build-time; injected only when all three are set) ───
#NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_SCRIPT_URL=/umami/gtnh-stats.js
#NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_HOST_URL=/umami
#NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=
